Inspired by the sour, spicy and sweet flavours of Thai cuisine, our veggie noodle
stir fry is guaranteed to keep weeknight dinners exciting.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Slice into rounds
about ½ cm thick. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Slice into thin strips.

Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the noodles.

Chop the @sugar snap peas{80%g} into 1cm pieces, trim the @pak choi{1}, slice in
half lengthways then slice widthways into 3cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lime{1/2}
and chop into wedges.

When the water for the noodles is boiling, stir in the @egg noodle nest{2} and
cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Drain the noodles in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over high heat.
Add the @sliced mushrooms{150%g}, leek and pepper to the pan. Cook until browned
and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

When the leeks, peppers and mushrooms are ready, lower the heat to medium. Add
the garlic, bok choy and sugar snaps. Stir and cook until the bok choy has
softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @Pad Thai paste{100%g} and @water{50%ml} and bring to a bubble. Add the
noodles and use #tongs{} to make sure the noodles are coated in the sauce and
continue cooking until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, transfer the @salted peanuts{25%g} to a #freezer bag{} and use the
bottom of a saucepan to smash them to a fine powder.

Mix the lime zest through the noodles. Season to taste with @salt{} and
@black pepper{} and get ready to serve.

Share the noodles and veggies between your plates. Don't leave any sauce
behind. Finish with a generous sprinkle of the smashed peanuts and a lime
wedge for squeezing over. Enjoy!